  "prompt": "Does the Tastemaker in Nestl\u00e9 Maggi really contain non-vegetarian substances?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Nestl\u00e9 Maggi's Tastemaker is typically marketed as a vegetarian product in many regions, especially in India. However, formulations can vary by country, and it's essential to check the ingredient list on the packaging for specific information. Sometimes, seasonings or flavorings may be derived from animal sources, but this is not standard for all versions of Maggi. If you have dietary restrictions or preferences, it's best to consult the product label or contact Nestl\u00e9 directly for the most accurate and up-to-date information regarding their products.",
